evidence: Technetium-99m, however, binds only weakly to the alumina column. That means if we pass a saline solution through the column, it will wash the technetium-99m out, while leaving the molybdenum-99 behind.

triples.evidence: Technetium-99m decays with a shorter half-life into stable technetium-99, releasing gamma radiation in the process.
